reviewText: My 5 year old is a big Cherry Jam fan, so when we saw this, it was a must buy.  I don't mind Strawberry Shortcake and friends, because it has good values and the dolls/cartoons are not over-sexualized.  This DVD has about four or five episodes--and it has auto-play as well, which is nice if you watch in the car.  (We bought it for a 4 hour drive.)  The first episode introduces you to Cherry Jam whose "real-life" persona is quite different from the one her PR time projects to the world.  Cherry just wants to be treated like a normal girl, not a superstar.  Another episode features Raspberry (Ra-Ra-Raspberry) being "discovered" and being offered a chance to be a big time fashion designer in Berry Big City.  I can't remember the other episodes, but they're all good.My daughter (and even her brothers) love this DVD.  I don't mind having it on in the background either.  The music is cute and upbeat.

reviewText: For those of you who, like me, are interested in which episodes of "Strawberry Shortcake's Berry Bitty Adventures" are contained on this DVD, here is the list:01. "Starlight, Star Bright" (November 19, 2011) - Strawberry's friends invite her favorite singer to surprise her for the opening of the Marketplace.02. "Practice Makes Perfect" (November 26, 2011) - Plum gets stage fright at Cherry Jam's recital for her new music students.03. "Top Talent" (December 3, 2011) - Lemon decides that she doesn't want any help with her performance in the first talent show of Berry Bitty City.04. "A Star Is Fashioned" (December 10, 2011) - Raspberry is scouted for her talent and has to decide if she wants to move to the big fashion world of the city.
summary: Contains 4 episodes of "Strawberry Shortcake's Berry Bitty Adventures"
